Can we add a few lines to EffectMaterialReader so it deals with additional types. Currently when looping through the KeyValuePairs it only checks for Textures misses other types such as Vector3,floats, and bool, which leads to an exception throw if using custom effects in ModelProcessor.

We just need to modify code in the foreach loop to check for other types, something like this

foreach (KeyValuePair<string, object> item in dict) 
{
     var parameter = effectMaterial.Parameters [item.Key];
      if (parameter != null) 
      {
# if WINRT

```
if (typeof(Texture).GetTypeInfo().IsAssignableFrom(item.Value.GetType().GetTypeInfo()))
                {
                  parameter.SetValue((Texture)item.Value);
                }
                else  if (typeof(Vector3).GetTypeInfo().IsAssignableFrom(item.Value.GetType().GetTypeInfo()))
                {
                    parameter.SetValue((Vector3)item.Value);
                }
                else  if (typeof(float).GetTypeInfo().IsAssignableFrom(item.Value.GetType().GetTypeInfo()))
                {
                   parameter.SetValue((float)item.Value);
                }
                else if (typeof(bool).GetTypeInfo().IsAssignableFrom(item.Value.GetType().GetTypeInfo()))
                {
                     parameter.SetValue((bool)item.Value);
                }
